# OpenUI Design Plan

## Variant 1

### Resolved inputs
- Topic: Autonomous ceramic kiln residency
- Offer: Application page for a six-week experimental kiln residency
- Audience: Ceramic artists exploring algorithmic firing and material systems
- Primary user action: Apply
- Deliverable: Single-file HTML with embedded CSS and JS
- Style direction: Industrial
- Tonal key: Topic-derived
- Icon policy: Minimal
- Proof assets: none
- Motion intensity: Rich but controlled

### Composition contract
- Hero archetype: immersive
- First-viewport structure: Oversized kiln-temperature headline on the left, live firing graph and clay-body specimen artifact on the right, primary and secondary CTAs below the copy, with the lower support cluster peeking into the first viewport.
- Primary visual/proof artifact: Topic-native kiln control surface and clay specimen, using only invented interface labels and no fake outcome metrics.
- Interaction behavior: Primary CTA marks the application as started; secondary CTA reveals the firing schedule structure.
- Reuse boundary: May share reset styles, navigation, and accessibility helpers with other variants; hero artifact, layout rhythm, and CTA behavior must be custom.

